Hello to all fellow hosts and guests!

I'm Mustafa, a dedicated family man and proud father of two beautiful girls. By profession, I'm a civil engineer, providing consultancy services, which imbues me with a meticulous attention to detail‚Äîa trait I extend to how I manage and maintain my cars.

I've been fortunate to travel extensively, taking road trips across the stunning landscapes of Turkey, the rugged terrains of Scotland, the historically rich regions of Italy, and the picturesque southern parts of the UK. These journeys have not only honed my driving skills but have also deepened my appreciation for the open road, the thrill of exploration, and the joy of driving.

Outside of my professional life and travel adventures, I have a keen interest in music and sports. You might often find me strumming my guitar or engaged in a spirited match of table tennis, one of my favourite pastimes. Music and driving often go hand in hand for me; there's nothing like the open road with my favourite tunes as the soundtrack.

While I'm yet undecided about my "dream car," I value the driving experience more than the badge on the hood. My priority is ensuring a comfortable, safe, and enjoyable ride, both for myself and for my Turo guests.

I take great pride in being a responsible and trustworthy host on Turo, and I treat every car and guest with the utmost respect. I understand the importance of trust in this community and am committed to upholding the standards we all expect.

Feel free to connect with me on [LinkedIn] https://www.linkedin.com/in/mustafaozgoren/, [Twitter] https://twitter.com/mustafaozgoren, [Facebook] https://www.facebook.com/mustafa.ozgoren.773 or [Instagram] @mustafaozgoren to get to know me better or share any mutual interests.

Looking forward to making your driving experience memorable and smooth!

Warm regards,
Mustafa
